The most common cluster heterogeneity measure used in malaria CRT sample size calculations was the coefficient of variation (k) (80% 52/65). 67.7% (44/65) of estimated cluster heterogeneity measures were estimated with no prior data while only 32.3% (21/65) were estimated using baseline or pilot study data. Lastly, only a minority of investigators retrospectively calculated cluster heterogeneity using trial data (20%, 13/65) (Table 2).
